<div class='documentTop'><div>
  
  
    <h1>Propositions and reports</h1>
  
  </div></div>
  

  <div class="documentBody" id="Tekstinnhold">   
  <div>
    <p>Propositions and reports are documents presented to the Storting. The documents are made by the ministries, and have the form of recommendations about what the Storting should decide.</p>
<p><a href="/en/dep/lmd/Documents/propositions-and-reports/reports-to-the-storting.html?id=660">Reports to the Storting</a> (St.meld.) are used when the Government wants to present issues for the Storting without proposing a decision. Reports to the Storting are often written in the form of a report of work done in a specific area, or a discussion of future politics. The reports, and the processing in the Storting, often form the basis of a proposition.</p>
<p>Propositions to the Storting (St.prp.) are used when the Government asks the Storting to make a decision that is not related to a law. This could be propositions related to the state budget or other propositions for decisions. </p>
<p>Propositions to the Odelsting (Ot.prp.) are used when the Government proposes new laws or cancellation of or amendments to existing laws. When the Storting processes law issues, it is split into the Odelsting and the Lagting.</p>
<p>Reports to the Odelsting (Ot.meld.) are used when the Government wants to address the Odelsting without proposing a law change. For example, a report to the Odelsting may be used to withdraw a proposition to the Odelsting. Reports to the Odelsting are seldom used.</p>
<p>On these pages you can find propositions and reports published by the Ministry of Agriculture and Food.</p>
  </div>
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
